<div class="row">
  <br>
</div>
<div style="background-color:transparent">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="twelve columns left" style="padding-top:2em;padding-bottom:2em">
      <h1 id='site-title'>Ruby Programming <small>Heroku Registry</small></h1>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="four columns">
    <div class="panel radius" style="background-color:#ff8">
      <h4>Link to Your App</h4>
      <p>Use this form to enter the URL for your Ruby Programming Heroku Rails Application. This form is
        collecting URLs from all of my Ruby courses at <a href="http://hackingthevalley.com/ccsf/ruby">City College of San Francisco</a> and <a href="http://hackingthevalley.com/csm/ruby">College of San Mateo.</a></p>
        <p>Enter your USERID and your HEROKU app.</p>
      </div>
      <p>Read the <a href="/welcome/assignment">assignment</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="eight columns" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;">
      <h3>Register your Heroku URL</h3>
      <%= form_for @student, :url => {:action => 'create'} do |f| %>
      <p>
        <%= f.label :COURSE %>
      </p>
      <p>
        <%= f.select :course, options_for_select(['Choose your course',['CS 132A','cs132a'],['CIS 113','cis113']]) %>
      </p>
      <p>
        <%= f.label :USERID %>
      </p>
      <p>
        <%= f.text_field :name, :placeholder =>'Your USERID' %>
      </p>
      <p>
        <%= f.label :URL %>
      </p>
      <p>
        <input type="url" name="url" placeholder="Heroku URL"/>
      </p>
      <input type="submit" class="round button" value="Register" />
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
<div style="margin:1em 0; height:40px;clear:both;"><br></div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="twelve columns" style="border:solid 8px #ccc">
    <h2><tt>your output will go here...</tt></h2>
    <h5 style="font-weight: bold">
      When you are finished this assignment, your app will display links to class Heroku web sites here. 
      Go to the <a href="http://polar-journey-7101.herokuapp.com">example</a> to see how your
      page should behave. 
    </h5>
  </div>
</div>
